        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;">Lemon Pepper Fish Fry</h2>
        <img style="padding-left:225px;width:400px;height:400px" src="https://content.osgnetworks.tv/gameandfishing/content/photos/grilled-lemon-pepper-trout-770x513.jpg" alt="Lemon Pepper Fish Fry">
        <div id="en">
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Ingredients:</p>
            <p style="color:#22facb;font-size:20px"> For the Curry:</p>
            <ul style="list-style-type:circle">
                <li> 4 fish fillets (such as tilapia, cod, or halibut)</li>
                <li> 2 lemons</li>
                <li> 2 tablespoons olive oil</li>
                <li> 2 teaspoons black pepper</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon salt</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon garlic powder</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon onion powder</li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon dried thyme</li>
                <li> Fresh parsley for garnish</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color:#f1860b;font-size:15pt;font-weight:bold;">Instructions:</p>
            <br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb"> 1. Prepare the Marinade:</li><ul>
                <li> In a bowl, combine the juice of one lemon, olive oil, black pepper, salt, garlic powder, onion powder.</li>
                <li>Mix these ingredients well to create a flavorful marinade.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">2. Marinate the Fish:</li><ul>
                <li> Place the fish fillets in a shallow dish or a resealable plastic bag.</li>
                <li> Pour the marinade over the fish, ensuring it's well-coated. Seal the bag or cover the dish.</li>
                <li> Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes. This allows the flavors to infuse into the fish.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">3. Preheat and Prepare Grill or Pan:</li><ul>
                <li> Preheat your grill to medium-high heat. </li>
                <li> If using a stovetop pan, heat it over medium-high heat and add a little oil to prevent sticking.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">4. Cook the Fish:</li><ul>
                <li> Place the marinated fish fillets on the grill or in the pan.</li>
                <li> Grill each side for about 3-4 minutes, or until the fish flakes easily with a fork and has a nice golden-brown color.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">5. Lemon Squeeze:</li><ul>
                <li> While the fish is cooking, cut the remaining lemon into wedges.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">6. Garnish and Serve:</li><ul>
                <li> Once the fish is cooked, remove it from the grill or pan.</li>
                <li> Squeeze fresh lemon juice over the cooked fish fillets for a burst of citrus flavor. </li>
                <li> Garnish with fresh parsley if desired.</li>

            </ul><br /><li style="text-decoration: underline;font-size:18px;list-style-type:none;color:#22facb">7. Serve:</li><ul>
                <li> Serve your Lemon Pepper Fish hot, accompanied by your choice of side dishes like steamed vegetables, rice, or a fresh salad.</li>

            </ul><p style="color:orange">Enjoy your zesty and flavorful Lemon Pepper Fish Fry!</p>
